Package: ARBO
Type: Package
Title: Rapid Spatial Clustering and Enriched Metabolite Discovery for MSI Data
Version: 0.5.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Xinyin Deng", email = "2386180950@qq.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides utilities for preprocessing, visualization, and spatial
    clustering of mass spectrometry imaging (MSI) metabolomics data. The
    package includes Python-based UMAP embedding through 'reticulate',
    multiple clustering methods, reconstruction and overlay of MSI images,
    and screening of spatially enriched metabolites. Two UMAP input
    strategies are supported: direct min-max scaled spectra and row-wise
    L2-normalized PCA scores computed with 'irlba'. Clustering results can
    be linked back to Cardinal MSI objects for downstream analysis, and
    spatially enriched metabolites can be screened by integrating spatial
    shrunken centroids and colocalization analysis.
